description: Join us for the Bhakti Club's General Interest Meeting at Tillet Hall (Room 230)! Discover the essence of Bhakti, a path of devotion and mindfulness, through engaging discussions, uplifting kirtan (devotional chanting), and an introduction to our community’s activities. Whether you're curious about spirituality, looking for a peaceful retreat from campus life, or hoping to connect with like-minded individuals, this meeting is the perfect place to start your journey. All are welcome—no prior experience needed! Afterwards, everyone comes together to have some fresh, homemade food (FREE), and network with people, rejuvenating ourselves for the upcoming week.

description: Welcome!   We (Rutgers Entrepreneurial Society) are hosting our General Interest Meeting for the semester at the Hatchery in Alexander Library, @ 6:30 PM on Friday, January 31st. We will discuss what the Rutgers Entrepreneurial Society stands for, and what you might gain from being a part of it.   2) ALL of our upcoming events for the semester, which will include keynote speakers, valuable skills needed in the field of entrepreneurship, and networking opportunities with some of the most ambitious and successful students at Rutgers so far.   3) Our events will include another year of Rutgers Shark Tank, and a Hackathon. Two great opportunities to meet entrepreneurial minds of Rutgers.   4) We won't discuss this, but there will be food!   Join us at the Hatchery in Alexander Library on Friday, January 31st @ 6:30 PM
